&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Anduril Industries is a defense technology company with a mission to transform U.S. and allied military capabilities with advanced technology. By bringing the expertise, technology, and business model of the 21st century’s most innovative companies to the defense industry, Anduril is changing how military systems are designed, built and sold. Anduril’s family of systems is powered by Lattice OS, an AI-powered operating system that turns thousands of data streams into a realtime, 3D command and control center. As the world enters an era of strategic competition, Anduril is committed to bringing cutting-edge autonomy, AI, computer vision, sensor fusion, and networking technology to the military in months, not years.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;ABOUT THE TEAM&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Anduril Imaging team develops&amp;nbsp;state-of-the-art&amp;nbsp;imaging systems across both hardware and software, deployed to tackle the most significant security challenges of America and its allies. The team is heavily involved in&amp;nbsp;utilizing&amp;nbsp;computer vision, perception, electro-optical, infrared, and sensor data to give our war fighters and allies an advantage.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;ABOUT THE JOB:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a skilled Mechanical Engineer to join our team, focusing on the design and development of Space-Based advanced complex electro-mechanical and structural and electronics packing. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in mechanical design, development, analysis, and manufacturing tasks on complex mechanical hardware including precision space structures and mechanisms in a program team environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop Space-Based&amp;nbsp;cutting-edge&amp;nbsp;infrared sensors.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design high-precision and complex space opto-mechanical&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and perform testing to show proof-of-design and/or qualification of new designs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize first principles physics as a basis for all decisions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build prototypes, analyze failures, and transition successful projects into production.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support critical hardware demonstrations with customers as needed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute in-depth and rigorous opto-mechanical and electro-mechanical designs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s&amp;nbsp;in mechanical engineering (BSME),&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;MS&amp;nbsp;with 5 plus years of&amp;nbsp;experience in design, hardware, or integrated product development and testing,&amp;nbsp;and excellent leadership/communication&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior or current experience with spaceflight imaging applications, especially related to optical systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency&amp;nbsp;in various CAD tools and openness to using new software, with the ability to create high-quality engineering drawings that meet industry standards.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong skills in material&amp;nbsp;selection,&amp;nbsp;finishing, component&amp;nbsp;sizing, system design, and troubleshooting.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional&amp;nbsp;analytical, troubleshooting, and root-cause analysis skills.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated hands-on fabrication skills.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to integrate electronic components into mechanical designs (motors, controllers, sensors, etc.).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with machining&amp;nbsp;and fabrication processes, sheet metal, injection molding, and 3D printing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of industry standards (e.g., ASME Y14.5 GD&amp;amp;T) and regulatory requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to drive projects from concept to completion&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal skills for documentation, presentations, and collaboration.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eligible to obtain and&amp;nbsp;maintain&amp;nbsp;an active U.S. Secret security clearance&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with complex optical system design, analysis, testing, and implementation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in working with engineering teams from conceptual through detailed design phases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in design of space-based mechanical structures, mechanisms, and electronics packaging along with engineering drawing development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in tolerance stack-up analysis for mechanical designs as well as GD&amp;amp;T&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with thermal management.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preference for Siemens NX &amp;amp; Teamcenter experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of DFMA.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
