&lt;p&gt;Avionics Production Control Schedulers develop and implement cohesive system tools to manage signals across all aspects of avionics production (design, supply chain, and operations) to drive efficiency and improvements. This position requires a combination of strong communication skills and an understanding of data analytics and manufacturing operations. Avionics Production Control Schedulers can flourish in a fast-paced and dynamic environment while guiding cross-functional teams. They show strong initiative and approach problem-solving with creativity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Scheduling:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage resource schedules and partner with the operations team to execute tight timelines while effectively communicating expected completion dates to customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead efforts to evaluate critical production processes (batching strategy, lead-time, workflow) and provide recommendations for sustainable solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in master scheduling process / integration-level decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize knowledge of upstream/downstream work centers to improve communication and efficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Analytics:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide recommendations on data inputs such as yield, lead times, and batching strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educate production on and drive improvements to internal MRP/ERP systems to ensure work is scheduled and prioritized accurately and efficiently, and resources are allocated appropriately&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create tools/processes that improve overall team scheduling methods, including streamlining inputs from and outputs to engineering, production, supply chain, and business management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the internal systems team to roll out large-scale projects as necessary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Reporting:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reduce time spent on manual data inputs into reporting tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve reporting formats to create better visibility to action owners- summarize data for tactical operations needs as well as executive level summaries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, improve, and analyze metrics that tie production to enterprise goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide daily visibility, weekly status, and monthly reviews on schedule performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BASIC QUALIFICATIONS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or 2+ years of manufacturing scheduling experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PREFERRED SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with SQL or Python&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience creating user-friendly, action-oriented visuals with Power BI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with lean principles, six sigma, and Kaizen concepts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project management professional certification OR 2+ years of practical experience with ERP/MRP systems in a production environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills, comfortable presenting to and influencing a variety of stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working both autonomously and as a team in a highly demanding and fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ADDITIONAL REQUIREMENTS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
